[h2 
	" The basic techniques
	$LF
	[a id=heading-892 
	]a
]h2
[h3 
	" Midair Tricks
	$LF
	[a id=heading-917 
	]a
]h3
[h4 
	" Jumping off sloped ground
	$LF
	[a id=heading-934 
	]a
]h4
[p 
	[img class=embedright src=/images/gameresources/megamanx/jumpdemo.png 
	]img
	$LF
	"If you jump while 
	[em 
		"walking
	]em
	" (not dashing) down a slope, your jump will be higher than normal. Sometimes, this trick allows you to gain access to areas usually only accessible through other means, but is more often used either to barely make it over a wall, or to jump earlier than normal to reach an overhang (if coming from the bottom of the slope), or to reach an overhang faster. Note that up-slopes are also down-slopes in disguise; when going up a slope, press the opposite direction for a couple frames and jump. The image to the right demonstrates how to clear a wall that is barely too high to dash-jump over.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"Sloped ground also gives a horizontal boost, whether walking (not dashing) downward on it or jumping off of it from walking. This trick is useful when you do not have the dash (in the first part of MMX1). There is no negative boost for walking or jumping up-slope.
	$LF
]p
[h4 
	" Water Hopping (MMX2, MMX3)
	$LF
	[a id=heading-1902 
	]a
]h4
[p 
	"By tapping jump while on any body of 
	$LF
	"water’s surface, it is possible to hop along 
	$LF
	"the water, giving you the ability 
	$LF
	"to cross it without ever having to dive down.  
	$LF
	"This technique can be enhanced by dashing onto 
	$LF
	"the surface of the water, so that distance 
	$LF
	"between water hops is made greater.
	$LF
]p
[h4 
	" Double triangle-hop
	$LF
	[a id=heading-2228 
	]a
]h4
[p 
	"You do not have to be right up against a wall to wall-jump; you only need
	$LF
	"to be within a few pixels (around 5 or 6) of the wall. So it is possible to wall-jump
	$LF
	"when right up against the wall, and then wall-jump again as you ascend off of it, allowing
	$LF
	"you to gain extra height.
	$LF
]p
[h4 
	" The Ride Armor's Jets (MMX2)
	$LF
	[a id=heading-2529 
	]a
]h4
[p 
	"By charging up and lunging off an edge, the ride armor maintains lunging speed while flying around. Tapping A (around once every 7 frames) makes the best use of the jets.
	$LF
]p
[h4 
	" Resetting the mid-air dash (MMX2)
	$LF
	[a id=heading-2733 
	]a
]h4
[p 
	"Use of the charged Speed Burner or Giga Crush, or grasping the bottom of an overhang as briefly as possible, resets the mid-air dash. Normally, you can only air-dash if you don't dash jump, and only air-dash once during the jump.
	$LF
]p
[h4 
	" Air-dashing close to the ceiling and grabbing the overhang from underneath (MMX2, MMX3)
	$LF
	[a id=heading-3001 
	]a
]h4
[p 
	"Because X's dash hitbox is shorter than his standing hitbox, X can air-dash very close to a ceiling if one side has an overhang. If the ceiling is U-shaped (two close overhangs), X can air-dash from one overhang and grab the other overhang from underneath.
	$LF
]p
[h3 
	" Luck Manipulation
	$LF
	[a id=heading-3351 
	]a
]h3
[h4 
	" Methods of luck manipulation
	$LF
	[a id=heading-3372 
	]a
]h4
[p 
	"Compared to the Mega Man series, it is harder to luck-manipulate. Simply doing a different dance won’t do it.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"Luck manipulation methods from best to worst:
	$LF
]p
[ul 
	[li 
		" Drag X down a wall so that dust sprites appear (the best method against bosses).
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Kill more (or less) enemies.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Position yourself differently or take damage (usually doesn't work).
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Wait a frame or two (or more).
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[p 
	"When to use luck-manipulation:
	$LF
]p
[ul 
	[li 
		" Item drops
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Boss actions
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Other
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[h4 
	" Dr. Light capsule manipulation (MMX2)
	$LF
	[a id=heading-3850 
	]a
]h4
[p 
	"For some reason, the capsule in Wheel Gator’s stage opens at variable times, any time from instantly to 2 seconds later. You want the capsule to open instantly.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"The reason is that, in these games (not just X2), the capsule opens only after the camera is centered properly. In Wheel Gator's stage, the screen periodically shakes.
	$LF
]p
[h3 
	" Weapon Glitches
	$LF
	[a id=heading-4223 
	]a
]h3
[h4 
	" Passing through enemies
	$LF
	[a id=heading-4242 
	]a
]h4
[p 
	"In some situations, the best way to get around an enemy is to go through it, without taking damage. Sometimes when an enemy is in continuous contact with a certain weapon, collision checks are ignored. 
	$LF
]p
[p 
	[b 
		"Charged Chameleon Sting
	]b
	" (MMX1): Designed that way.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	[b 
		"Charged Rolling Shield
	]b
	" (MMX1): Even if an enemy destroys the charged Rolling Shield by contact, it won’t do collision checks on X for about 7 frames.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	[b 
		"Charged Speed Burner
	]b
	" (MMX2): X’s Speed Burner dash allows passing through all non-underwater enemies.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	[b 
		"Silk Shot
	]b
	" (MMX2): Sometimes, the shrapnel from this weapon stops collision checks until the enemy is already destroyed.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	[b 
		"Tornado Fang
	]b
	" (MMX3): If an enemy can be hit by Tornado Fang, it won’t do collision checks for about 15 frames.
	$LF
]p
[h4 
	" Passing through the giant fish’s laser in Bubble Crab’s stage (MMX2)
	$LF
	[a id=heading-5032 
	]a
]h4
[p 
	"If you use charged Speed Burner, you may be able to gain enough horizontal speed to pass through the fish’s laser unharmed (poor collision checking). Normally, X cannot pass through the laser.
	$LF
]p
[h4 
	" Dashing uncharged X-Buster
	$LF
	[a id=heading-5298 
	]a
]h4
[p 
	[a class=intlink href=/Megamanx/Dashshotcharged.png 
		"right
	]a
	"By dashing and then shooting uncharged X-Buster shots, the first that comes out does more damage than when not dashing. Specifically, in X & X2 only, this shot does 2 damage to bosses, rather than the normal 1 (this does not hold true against a couple bosses in X2, or against X3 bosses except the intro boss which takes 4 instead of 3). The technique works 
	$LF
	"as long as you are in some type of dash movement, including jumping after dashing, and dashing off a ledge.
	$LF
]p
[h4 
	" Shooting while charged and remaining charged (MMX1, MMX2)
	$LF
	[a id=heading-5832 
	]a
]h4
[p 
	"In MMX1, if you fire just as you regain control of X and you are charged up, you shoot a normal shot while keeping the charge (for MMX2 it is just before control). This trick works with any weapon. A possible use is to gain an extra second to charge up when only partially charged.
	$LF
]p
[h4 
	" Strike Chain (MMX2)
	$LF
	[a id=heading-6176 
	]a
]h4
[p 
	[img class=embedright src=/images/gameresources/megamanx/Strikechainfloor.png 
	]img
	"The Strike Chain is a weapon and grappling hook with many properties that are important in a speedrun:
	$LF
]p
[p 
	[b 
		"The Strike Chain pulls X toward a wall
	]b
	". This method of horizontal movement is one of the fastest in the game, even though it is brief and limited. When charged, it pulls X even faster and from further away.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	[b 
		"As the Strike Chain pulls X, vertical speed is preserved
	]b
	". X’s speed only resets if he reaches the end of the Strike Chain. If the Strike Chain pull is cancelled before then (by pressing opposite direction to the pull), X drops off the Strike Chain at the same vertical downward speed as when before being pulled, or even jump upward slightly if X was jumping upward before being pulled.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	[b 
		"X can enter thin floors with Strike Chain
	]b
	". If X fires a Strike Chain prior to climbing down a ladder, the Strike Chain will continue and grab the interior of a thin floor when X climbs down. As a result, X is pulled into the floor. When X is inside the floor, it functions as a ladder. This trick does not work on floors with walls underneath.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	[b 
		"The Strike Chain can reset vertical speed
	]b
	". If a Strike Chain grapples something and either pulls X completely or not at all, it resets vertical speed. Simply using Strike Chain close to an overhang resets vertical speed while keeping dash movement.
	$LF
]p
[h4 
	" Beam Saber (MMX3)
	$LF
	[a id=heading-7569 
	]a
]h4
[p 
	[img class=embedright src=/images/gameresources/megamanx/Xswordslash.png 
	]img
	"The Beam Saber (or “Beam Sabre”) is the secret weapon that kills bosses in two hits. Yet much time can be saved from efficient usage:
	$LF
]p
[ul 
	[li 
		" The Beam Saber will not fire until the charged shot is gone. The fastest way to clear a charged shot is to shoot it into a nearby enemy (the boss). It is necessary to prevent the boss from being harmed by this shot due to its 60-frame invincibility, so pre-hit the boss to make it flash beforehand in such a way that the charged shot does not harm the boss but the sword does. If it is not possible to do so in this manner, the next fastest way is to dash while shooting the charged shot off the edge of the screen.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" The Beam Saber strikes the fastest on the first frame on which it appears, which is behind X. X draws the Beam Saber one frame faster if he stands on the ground to start swinging than when in midair.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" To charge up a second Beam Saber, it is fastest to take damage after hitting with the first Beam Saber so that the slash animation is cancelled. Post-slash animation has no effect on charging.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" To cancel either the post-slash animation or the Beam Saber altogether before it slashes, quickly switch weapons. Useful for regaining full control of X.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" The Beam Saber allows charging of all weapons to the yellow level, even without X-Buster upgrade. This allows firing a special weapon and charging to prepare a Beam Saber.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[h4 
	" Beam Saber/Charged X-Buster double-jump (MMX3)
	$LF
	[a id=heading-9025 
	]a
]h4
[p 
	"If X/Zero swings his Beam Saber or shoots a pink/red/green charged shot either during the first part of a wall-jump or during a vertical air dash, and jump is held down, X immediately jumps up as if he jumped from ground. Combined with switching weapons to regain control, X can gain additional height and even air-dash again (Zero cannot switch weapons so requires being hit). Note that this trick alone cannot put X in dash movement.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"YouTube video (air dash): 
	[a class=extlink href=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DqgAp3cMNJU rel=nofollow 
		"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DqgAp3cMNJU
	]a
	$LF
]p
[h4 
	" Zero’s continuous Beam Saber (MMX3)
	$LF
	[a id=heading-9584 
	]a
]h4
[p 
	"During the time when you control Zero, if you have Zero slash with the Beam Saber, then rapidly jump (once every 4 or 5 frames) Zero will keep the sword out and it will continue to damage enemies. This trick is not particularly useful, mainly due to not needing to control Zero for most of the game.
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	[br 
